      "question_id": "q1",
      "answer": "'Probability input' should be interpreted as testing the outcome selector dropdown that displays marginal probabilities (e.g., 'Yes @ 65.0%'). EventTradePanel has NO probability slider or input field — it only has a side toggle (buy/sell) and an outcome <select> dropdown where each option displays the marginal probability. TradingPanel has a slider for editing probability; EventTradePanel only displays probabilities in the dropdown options and as a 'Price: X%' label. The test should cover selecting an outcome and verifying the displayed price, not a slider interaction.",
