      "answer": "crypto.randomUUID() works natively in the test environment without mocking. The existing TradingPanel.test.tsx (line 163) and ConditionalEditor.test.tsx (line 331) both assert `idempotencyKey` is defined without mocking crypto, confirming vitest/jsdom on modern Node.js supports it. The test should follow the same pattern: assert `call.payload.idempotencyKey` is defined (toBeDefined()) without mocking crypto. No polyfill or mock is needed.",
